
LICENSING INFORMATION IS IN THE DIRECTORY LEGAL_AND_FAQ. PLEASE
READ THIS BEFORE USING ANY OF THE RTLINUX DISTRIBUTION.

RTLinux is a hard real-time kernel that runs  Linux as its idle thread.
More information can be found at http://www.rtlinux-gpl.org/
and http://www.fsmlabs.com/

Installation instructions can be found in doc/INSTALLATION.
A quick introduction to RTLinux, some installation instructions
and a short tutorial on writing own modules can be found here:
www.tldp.org/HOWTO/RTLinux-HOWTO

If you are upgrading from previous versions of RTLinux, please read the
file doc/upgrading.txt.

For commercial support email support@fsmlabs.com
For free support try the mailing list: rtl@rtlinux.org. People on the
list are very helpful, if you are nice to them.

Finite State Machine Labs Inc. (FSMLabs) created and maintains
RTLinux.
